{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"ryadSalihin","displayName":"Riyad as-Salihin","type":"quotes","language":"English","edition":"Imam An-Nawawi, Gardens of the Righteous","primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Islamic","audienceTags":["hadith","devotional"],"sortPriority":26,"itemCount":50,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"browseOrder":"sequence","groupingLevels":["chapter","hadith"],"groupingLabels":["Chapter","Hadith"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Hadith_RiyadSalihin.json","version":"1.0"},"data":[{"id":"riyad-1-1","text":"The reward of deeds depends upon the intentions and every person will get the reward according to what he has intended.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 1, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":0},{"id":"riyad-1-2","text":"Allah the Exalted says: 'Spend (O man), and I shall spend on you.'","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 1, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":1},{"id":"riyad-1-3","text":"Verily, Allah has one hundred mercies. He distributed one of them among all creatures, through which they are kind to one another. He has kept ninety-nine mercies for the Day of Judgment.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 1, Hadith 3","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","hadith":"3"},"sequenceIndex":2},{"id":"riyad-1-4","text":"The best of people are those that bring most benefit to the rest of mankind.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 1, Hadith 4","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","hadith":"4"},"sequenceIndex":3},{"id":"riyad-2-1","text":"Allah is happier with the repentance of his servant when he repents than one of you would be if he lost his riding camel in a barren land, then found it again.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 2, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":4},{"id":"riyad-2-2","text":"Were you not to commit sins, Allah would create people who would commit sins and then seek forgiveness from Him; He would forgive them.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 2, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":5},{"id":"riyad-2-3","text":"All the sons of Adam are sinners, but the best of sinners are those who are most often repentant.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 2, Hadith 3","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","hadith":"3"},"sequenceIndex":6},{"id":"riyad-3-1","text":"Be kind, for whenever kindness becomes part of something, it beautifies it. Whenever it is taken from something, it leaves it tarnished.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 3, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":7},{"id":"riyad-3-2","text":"Allah does not judge you for your outward appearance and your wealth, but He looks at your hearts and your deeds.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 3, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":8},{"id":"riyad-3-3","text":"The strong man is not the one who overcomes the people by his strength, but the strong man is the one who controls himself while in anger.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 3, Hadith 3","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","hadith":"3"},"sequenceIndex":9},{"id":"riyad-3-4","text":"Patience is illumination.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 3, Hadith 4","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","hadith":"4"},"sequenceIndex":10},{"id":"riyad-3-5","text":"The real patience is at the first stroke of calamity.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 3, Hadith 5","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","hadith":"5"},"sequenceIndex":11},{"id":"riyad-4-1","text":"Adhere to truthfulness, for truthfulness leads to righteousness, and righteousness leads to Paradise.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 4, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":12},{"id":"riyad-4-2","text":"Avoid falsehood, for falsehood leads to wickedness, and wickedness leads to the Hell-fire.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 4, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":13},{"id":"riyad-5-1","text":"Take advantage of five before five: your youth before your old age, your health before your illness, your wealth before your poverty, your free time before your preoccupation, and your life before your death.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 5, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":14},{"id":"riyad-5-2","text":"The most beloved deeds to Allah are those done regularly, even if they are few.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 5, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":15},{"id":"riyad-5-3","text":"Every good deed is a charity. What you put into the mouth of your wife is a charity. What you put into the mouth of your child is a charity.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 5, Hadith 3","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","hadith":"3"},"sequenceIndex":16},{"id":"riyad-5-4","text":"Whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day should speak good or remain silent.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 5, Hadith 4","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","hadith":"4"},"sequenceIndex":17},{"id":"riyad-6-1","text":"The world is a prison for the believer and a paradise for the disbeliever.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 6, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"6","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":18},{"id":"riyad-6-2","text":"Be in this world as though you were a stranger or a wayfarer.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 6, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"6","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":19},{"id":"riyad-7-1","text":"Fear Allah wherever you are, follow up a bad deed with a good deed and it will blot it out, and treat people with good character.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 7, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"7","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":20},{"id":"riyad-7-2","text":"If you were to rely upon Allah with the reliance He is due, He would provide for you just as He provides for the birds.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 7, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"7","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":21},{"id":"riyad-8-1","text":"Be merciful to others, and Allah will be merciful to you.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 8, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"8","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":22},{"id":"riyad-8-2","text":"Allah is merciful to those who are merciful to others. Be merciful to those on earth, the One in the heavens will be merciful to you.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 8, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"8","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":23},{"id":"riyad-8-3","text":"A smile to your brother is charity. A word of good advice is charity. Every step you take toward the prayer is charity. Removing a stone or thorn or bone from the road is charity.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 8, Hadith 3","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"8","hadith":"3"},"sequenceIndex":24},{"id":"riyad-9-1","text":"Whoever wishes to have his provision expanded and his age lengthened should maintain family ties.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 9, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"9","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":25},{"id":"riyad-9-2","text":"The one who maintains family ties is not the one who does so because his relatives do the same; rather, the one who maintains family ties is the one who does so even if his relatives cut ties with him.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 9, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"9","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":26},{"id":"riyad-10-1","text":"None of you will believe until you love for your brother what you love for yourself.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 10, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"10","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":27},{"id":"riyad-10-2","text":"Allah loves that when one of you does something, he does it with excellence.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 10, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"10","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":28},{"id":"riyad-11-1","text":"By Allah, he does not believe! By Allah, he does not believe! By Allah, he does not believe! It was asked: Who is that, O Allah's Messenger? He said: That person whose neighbor does not feel safe from his evil.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 11, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"11","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":29},{"id":"riyad-11-2","text":"Make the most of five things before five things: your life before your death, your health before your sickness, your free time before you become busy, your youth before your old age, and your wealth before your poverty.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 11, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"11","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":30},{"id":"riyad-12-1","text":"The best of you is he who is most beneficial to others.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 12, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"12","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":31},{"id":"riyad-12-2","text":"Feed the hungry, visit the sick, and free the captive.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 12, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"12","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":32},{"id":"riyad-12-3","text":"Make things easy and do not make them difficult, cheer people up and do not repulse them.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 12, Hadith 3","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"12","hadith":"3"},"sequenceIndex":33},{"id":"riyad-13-1","text":"The just will be seated upon pulpits of light, those who are just in their ruling, in their dealings, and in all that they do.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 13, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"13","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":34},{"id":"riyad-13-2","text":"Whoever removes one of the hardships of a believing soul, Allah will remove from him one of the distresses on the Day of Judgment.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 13, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"13","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":35},{"id":"riyad-14-1","text":"Do not envy one another; do not hate one another; and be brothers, O servants of Allah.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 14, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"14","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":36},{"id":"riyad-14-2","text":"Shall I not tell you something better than fasting, praying and giving charity? It is making peace between people.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 14, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"14","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":37},{"id":"riyad-15-1","text":"Whoever follows a path in the pursuit of knowledge, Allah will make easy for him a path to Paradise.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 15, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"15","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":38},{"id":"riyad-15-2","text":"The best of you is he who learns the Quran and teaches it.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 15, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"15","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":39},{"id":"riyad-16-1","text":"Look at those who are beneath you and do not look at those who are above you, for it is more suitable that you should not consider as less the blessing of Allah upon you.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 16, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"16","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":40},{"id":"riyad-16-2","text":"He who does not thank people, does not thank Allah.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 16, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"16","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":41},{"id":"riyad-17-1","text":"Charity given to a poor person is just charity, but charity given to a relative has two rewards: charity and upholding family ties.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 17, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"17","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":42},{"id":"riyad-17-2","text":"Protect yourself from the Hell-fire even by giving half a date-fruit in charity.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 17, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"17","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":43},{"id":"riyad-18-1","text":"Every soul will taste death. And We test you with evil and with good as trial; and to Us you will be returned.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 18, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"18","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":44},{"id":"riyad-18-2","text":"Live in this world as if you are a stranger or a traveler. Consider yourself as one of the inhabitants of the graves.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 18, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"18","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":45},{"id":"riyad-19-1","text":"Purify yourself, for Islam is built on purity.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 19, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"19","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":46},{"id":"riyad-19-2","text":"Prayer is a light. Charity is a proof. Patience is illumination.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 19, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"19","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":47},{"id":"riyad-20-1","text":"The best form of dhikr (remembrance of Allah) is La ilaha illallah, and the best supplication is Al-Hamdulillah.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 20, Hadith 1","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"20","hadith":"1"},"sequenceIndex":48},{"id":"riyad-20-2","text":"Maintain equity, for equity is a kind of balance given to the community.","author":"Prophet Muhammad (PBUH)","source":"Riyad as-Salihin, Chapter 20, Hadith 2","tags":["hadith","islam","language:english","collection:riyad"],"groups":{"chapter":"20","hadith":"2"},"sequenceIndex":49}]}